<p>Hey. <br /> <br />I have a question!&nbsp;&nbsp;*Blush* <br /> <br />I attained level forty-nine last night and duly sat down to scribe my new spells.  Some are every bit as delightful as anticipated and others are a little dissapointing.  <i>(Ignite blood coulda been a bit faster!  Still, it's an awesome spell none-the-less.  (And I get envenomed bolt in another coupla levels.  That has damage and speed all wrapped up!  *Cackle*))</i> <br /> <br />Anyhow, my new pet appears to be casting a fear spell!?!  I've never heard, or seen anything about this, before.  (It casts a spells with the same green skull animation as Fear.  (And asystole also, admittedly.))  Does anyone know what this is?  Is it just the lifetap, but with an improved animation, or what?   <br /> <br />I haven't tested it enough, to see what it is as yet.  (I was hunting spiders in the Field of Bone.  They don't exactly last long enough to be sure.  *Grin*  No complaints there!) <br /> <br />So, I wait for your wisdom.  Just what is my pet doin'? <br /> <br />Thanks all. <br /> <br />AlAaraaf. <br /> <br /> <br /><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Feb  1 10:05:50 2002</em></p>
